By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Diri Duoye, has been sworn in as the Governor of Bayelsa State. Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo had earlier taken oath of office as deputy governor of the state. Recall that the supreme court yesterday sacked the All Progressives Congress governor-elect for certificate forgery. Details later …